			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hello,
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">If I use only Textual Confirmation and moderate my board manually, will that be effective?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
As you are going to allow anonymous postings, no. You also have to install Links Rejector to stop spam in the guest postings.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Can TC work on one form or is it a two form process?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
TC is a one-form process.
<br />

<br />
Thanks for questions, now I have ideas how to re-write texts and suggestions. Draft short version:
<br />

<br />
There are two alternative types of setup:
<br />

<br />
1) Textual Confirmation plus Links Rejector, or
<br />
2) Advanced Textual Confirmation.
<br />

<br />
The first gives better integration with phpBB, but the second is much easier in setup and maintenance. If you don't know what to use, use Advanced Textual Confirmation.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I'd just like it to be simple and fast to post.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
This forum is protected by Advanced Textual Confirmation only. As you've already posted two messages, you can estimate if it's simple and fast.
<br />

<br />
By the way, how have you found it? Was it simple and fast?<br />_________________<br />Oleg Parashchenko, bbAntiSpam
